Bo draws a 1-by-1 square (green). He begins a spiral by adding on a 2-by-1 rectangle (blue), then a 3-by-1 rectangle (pink), etc. Each rectangle is one unit longer than the previous rectangle added. What will be the perimeter of the spiral after the 8th rectangle is added?

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5]
% Green square (1) - center
\fill[green!60] (2,2) rectangle (3,3);
\draw (2,2) rectangle (3,3);
\node at (2.5,2.5) {1};

% Blue rectangle (2) - on top of green
\fill[blue!40] (2,3) rectangle (3,4);
\draw (2,3) rectangle (3,4);
\node at (2.5,3.5) {2};

% Pink rectangle (3) - to the right
\fill[pink] (3,2) rectangle (4,4);
\draw (3,2) rectangle (4,3);
\draw (3,3) rectangle (4,4);
\node at (3.5,3) {3};

% Orange rectangle (4) - at the bottom
\fill[orange!60] (1,1) rectangle (4,2);
\draw (1,1) rectangle (2,2);
\draw (2,1) rectangle (3,2);
\draw (3,1) rectangle (4,2);
\node at (2.5,1.5) {4};

% Rectangle (5) - on the left
\fill[white] (1,1) rectangle (2,4);
\draw (1,1) rectangle (2,2);
\draw (1,2) rectangle (2,3);
\draw (1,3) rectangle (2,4);
\node at (1.5,2.5) {5};
\end{tikzpicture}
